FBIS3-10159 "drlat041_t_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 Venezuela Caldera Reports on Effort To Face Financial Crisis PA2802231594 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in Spanish 1550 GMT 28 Feb 94 PA2802231594 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From "The News" newscast] [Excerpt] President Rafael Caldera has reported that the suspension of economic guarantees is directed at dealing with the country's financial crisis. Regarding the Value Added Tax [VAT], Caldera said very soon the government will present to Congress a general tax reform bill that calls for the definite elimination of the VAT on consumers, substituting it with other collection mechanisms that will allow those who have more to pay more. This announcement was welcomed by the community. [passage omitted]
